gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pacers 134, 76ers 122
gameRecap.excerpt: The Pacers defeated the 76ers, 134-122. Pascal Siakam recorded 26 points, 13 rebounds and 10 assists for the Pacers, his first triple-double of the season and sixth of his career, while Myles Turner added 20 points and nine rebounds in the victory. Joel Embiid tallied his 22nd consecutive game with 30+ points, putting up 31 points and seven rebounds for the 76ers in the losing effort. The Pacers improve to 25-20 on the season, while the 76ers snap a six-game winning streak as they fall to 29-14.
